sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client / KServe Gateway
    participant API as vLLM OpenAI Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP(S)
    participant Auth as AuthenticationMiddleware<br/>SHA256 Constant-Time
    participant Input as InputProcessor<br/>Tokenizer
    participant Core as EngineCore<br/>Scheduler + KV Cache
    participant Runner as CPU Model Runner<br/>PyTorch CPU
    participant Output as OutputProcessor<br/>Detokenizer

    Note over Client,Output: Flow 1: Inference Request Processing

    Client->>API: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer API Key
    API->>Auth: Validate token<br/>SHA256 hash compare
    Auth-->>API: 200 OK / 401 Unauthorized

    API->>Input: Parse & preprocess request
    Input->>Input: Tokenize text<br/>(HuggingFace transformers)
    Input->>Core: Tokenized input + params

    Core->>Core: Schedule request<br/>Continuous batching<br/>KV cache allocation
    Core->>Runner: Execute batch<br/>CPU tensors
    Runner->>Runner: PyTorch forward pass<br/>CPU backend

    Runner-->>Core: Logits / tokens
    Core-->>Output: Generated tokens

    alt Streaming (SSE)
        loop Token by token
            Output-->>API: Token chunk
            API-->>Client: data: {"choices":[...]}
        end
        API-->>Client: data: [DONE]
    else Non-streaming
        Output-->>API: Complete response
        API-->>Client: JSON response
    end

    Note over Client,Output: Flow 2: Model Loading (Startup)

    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Disk as Local Disk<br/>Model Cache

    API->>HF: GET model config + weights<br/>Auth: Bearer HF_TOKEN<br/>TLS 1.2+
    HF-->>API: Model artifacts
    API->>Disk: Cache model files
    Disk->>Runner: Load weights into CPU memory<br/>PyTorch parameter loader

    Note over Client,Output: Flow 3: Observability

    participant Prom as Prometheus Scraper
    participant OTLP as OTLP Collector

    Prom->>API: GET /metrics<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    API-->>Prom: Prometheus metrics

    API->>OTLP: Export traces<br/>gRPC (insecure default)
